This paper deals with computer vision techniques for detecting trip hazards on construction sites, which falls under the category of computer vision (cs.CV) and robotics (cs.RO). The paper also discusses the use of machine learning algorithms for this task, which could fall under the categories of machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Additionally, the paper mentions the use of publicly available datasets, which could fall under the category of information retrieval (cs.IR).
